### Configure Globber from Action Inputs (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/actions/toolkit/blob/main/packages/glob/README.md

This snippet shows how to consume action inputs for file patterns and the 'followSymbolicLinks' option, dynamically configuring the globber. It demonstrates converting the input string to a boolean for the option.

```javascript
const core = require('@actions/core')
const glob = require('@actions/glob')

const globOptions = {
  followSymbolicLinks: core.getInput('follow-symbolic-links').toUpper() !== 'FALSE'
}
const globber = glob.create(core.getInput('files'), globOptions)
for await (const file of globber.globGenerator()) {
  console.log(file)
}
```

