### Mocking Octokit Issue Creation with Nock (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/actions/toolkit/blob/main/docs/github-package.md

Mocks a POST request to create an issue comment using nock. This is useful for testing GitHub Actions that interact with the GitHub API. It intercepts requests to 'https://api.github.com/repos/foo/bar/issues/10/comments' with a specific JSON body and returns a 200 OK response. Ensure nock is installed as a dev dependency (`npm install nock --save-dev`).

```typescript
const nock = require('nock');
const path = require('path');

describe('action test suite', () => {
  it('It posts a comment on an opened issue', async () => {
    const welcomeMessage = 'hello';
    const repoToken = 'token';
    process.env['INPUT_WELCOME-MESSAGE'] = welcomeMessage;
    process.env['INPUT_REPO-TOKEN'] = repoToken;

    process.env['GITHUB_REPOSITORY'] = 'foo/bar';
    process.env['GITHUB_EVENT_PATH'] = path.join(__dirname, 'payload.json');

    nock('https://api.github.com')
      .persist()
      .post('/repos/foo/bar/issues/10/comments', '{"body":"hello"}')
      .reply(200);

    const main = require('../src/main');

    await main.run();
  });
});
```
